        <bcl:section id="d2e611">
          <bcl:marginalnote>Classes of motor vehicles subject to temporary exemption from emissions inspection</bcl:marginalnote>
          <bcl:num>2.1</bcl:num>
          <bcl:text>The following classes of motor vehicles are exempt from the requirement to be certified for motor vehicle compliance under section 48 of the <in:doc>Motor Vehicle Act</in:doc> for the period, and on the conditions, specified:</bcl:text>
          <bcl:paragraph id="d2e625">
            <bcl:num>a</bcl:num>
            <bcl:text>a vehicle that has failed the emissions test if</bcl:text>
            <bcl:subparagraph id="d2e634">
              <bcl:num>i</bcl:num>
              <bcl:text>the failed vehicle has not been issued with a licence under section 50 (4) of the <in:doc>Motor Vehicle Act</in:doc>,</bcl:text>
            </bcl:subparagraph>
            <bcl:subparagraph id="d2e647">
              <bcl:num>ii</bcl:num>
              <bcl:text>the owner of the failed vehicle transfers the licence from another vehicle to the failed vehicle and the transferred licence has a term of less than 4 months remaining on it, and</bcl:text>
            </bcl:subparagraph>
            <bcl:subparagraph id="d2e656">
              <bcl:num>iii</bcl:num>
              <bcl:text>the failed vehicle does not receive 2 consecutive exemptions under this paragraph;</bcl:text>
            </bcl:subparagraph>
          </bcl:paragraph>
          <bcl:paragraph id="d2e665">
            <bcl:num>b</bcl:num>
            <bcl:text>an unlicensed vehicle newly purchased outside rating territory D, E or H, for a period not to exceed 12 months from the date of purchase;</bcl:text>
          </bcl:paragraph>
          <bcl:paragraph id="d2e674">
            <bcl:num>c</bcl:num>
            <bcl:text>a vehicle licensed in British Columbia that is located outside rating territory D, E or H at the time of the licence renewal, for a period not to exceed 3 months and only once in a 12 month period;</bcl:text>
          </bcl:paragraph>
          <bcl:paragraph id="d2e683">
            <bcl:num>d) and (e</bcl:num>
            <bcl:text>Repealed. [B.C. Reg. 403/2000.]</bcl:text>
          </bcl:paragraph>
          <bcl:paragraph id="d2e692">
            <bcl:num>f</bcl:num>
            <bcl:text>an even numbered model year vehicle, that is a 1992 model year or a newer model year vehicle, for the period from January 1, 2001 through December 31, 2001, if the inspection result in the previous year was a pass or a conditional pass.</bcl:text>
          </bcl:paragraph>
          <bcl:hnote>[en. B.C. Reg. 96/93; am. B.C. Reg. 403/2000.]</bcl:hnote>
        </bcl:section>
        <bcl:section id="d2e706">
          <bcl:marginalnote>Areas of British Columbia in which motor vehicles are exempt from emission inspection certification</bcl:marginalnote>
          <bcl:num>3</bcl:num>
          <bcl:text>A motor vehicle is exempt from the requirement to be certified for motor vehicle compliance under section 48 of the <in:doc>Motor Vehicle Act</in:doc> if the vehicle is registered and licensed in insurance rating territory D, E, F, G, H, L, N, P, R, S, V, W, X, Y or Z as set out in the Basic Insurance Tariff as filed by the Insurance Corporation of British Columbia with the British Columbia Utilities Commission.</bcl:text>
          <bcl:hnote>[am. B.C. Regs. 142/93; 246/93; 41/96; 194/96; 161/2007, s. 1; 267/2014.]</bcl:hnote>
        </bcl:section>
        <bcl:section id="d2e724">
          <bcl:marginalnote>Aircare</bcl:marginalnote>
          <bcl:num>4</bcl:num>
          <bcl:text>Insurance rating territory H as set out in the Basic Insurance Tariff as filed by the Insurance Corporation of British Columbia with the British Columbia Utilities Commission.</bcl:text>
          <bcl:hnote>[en. B.C. Reg. 277/99; am. B.C. Reg. 161/2007, s. 2.]</bcl:hnote>
        </bcl:section>
        <bcl:section id="d2e740">
          <bcl:marginalnote>January 2000 exemption</bcl:marginalnote>
          <bcl:num>5</bcl:num>
          <bcl:text>If, during the month of January, 2000, the president or a vice president of the Insurance Corporation of British Columbia declares that the Insurance Corporation of British Columbia or the Greater Vancouver Transportation Authority is unable to perform, record or communicate certification for motor vehicle compliance under section 48 of the <in:doc>Motor Vehicle Act</in:doc> because of a system failure that affects the corporation or authority, all motor vehicles are exempt from the programs described in section 50 (1) and (1.2) of the <in:doc>Motor Vehicle Act</in:doc>, from the date of that declaration until February 1, 2000.</bcl:text>
          <bcl:hnote>[en. B.C. Reg. 380/99, s. (b).]</bcl:hnote>
        </bcl:section>
        <bcl:footnote>
          <bcl:num>1</bcl:num>
          <bcl:text>authority changed to Lieutenant Governor in Council by 1996-14-24</bcl:text>
        </bcl:footnote>
        <reg:provisionsnote>[Provisions relevant to the enactment of this regulation: <in:doc> Motor Vehicle Act</in:doc>, R.S.B.C. 1996, c. 318, section 50 (2)]</reg:provisionsnote>
      </reg:content>
    </reg:regulation>
  </change>
  <change section="1">
    <changenote eff="March 2, 2016">Section 1 definition of "model year" BEFORE repealed by BC Reg <amendingreg>59/2016</amendingreg>, effective March 2, 2016.</changenote>
    <bcl:definition id="d2e110">
      <bcl:text>
        <in:term>model year</in:term> has the same meaning as in Division 29 of B.C. Reg. 26/58, the Motor Vehicle Act Regulations.</bcl:text>
    </bcl:definition>
  </change>
  <change section="3">
    <changenote eff="January 1, 2015">Section 3 BEFORE amended by BC Reg <amendingreg>267/2014</amendingreg>, effective January 1, 2015.</changenote>
    <bcl:section id="d2e7061">
      <bcl:marginalnote>Areas of British Columbia in which motor vehicles are exempt from emission inspection certification</bcl:marginalnote>
      <bcl:num>3</bcl:num>
      <bcl:text>A motor vehicle is exempt from the requirement to be certified for motor vehicle compliance under section 48 of the <in:doc>Motor Vehicle Act</in:doc> if the vehicle is registered and licensed in insurance rating territory F, G, L, N, P, R, S, V, W, X, Y or Z as set out in the Basic Insurance Tariff as filed by the Insurance Corporation of British Columbia with the British Columbia Utilities Commission.</bcl:text>
      <bcl:hnote>[am. B.C. Regs. 142/93; 246/93; 41/96; 194/96; 161/2007, s. 1.]</bcl:hnote>
    </bcl:section>
  </change>
